Prior to raping the girl, Alves befriended her by posing as a teenager.
He was charged in January 2013 and convicted in June the same year.
Staffordshire Police worked with the UK National Crime Agency and Brazilian authorities to catch Alves, who was arrested earlier this month.
He will remain in custody until the Brazil High Court rules on his expected extradition to the UK, said police.
At the time of arrest, Alves lived at Aneurin Bevan Place in Rugeley and worked in Stafford.
